James May and Richard Hammond met with Top Gear executive producer Andy Wilman today . 
  It was their first public appearance together since Jeremy Clarkson was sacked last month . 
  Mr Wilman has quit the BBC and is free to reunite with the team on a rival channel . 
  He was seen outside Clarkson's home in west London just hours before resigning . 
  Earlier today May said it would be 'lame' to return to Top Gear without Clarkson . 
  He said the BBC would be ‘stupid’ to try a new series with him and Hammond . 
  BBC2 boss Kim Shillinglaw has been tasked with finding a replacement for Clarkson . 
